ion counter** — `static AtomicU64` incremented in `open_sqlite_readonly()` (line 1685), with `reset`/`get` helpers. Logs total connection count.\n\n2. **`open_sqlite_readonly()`** (line 1685) — Increment counter. Optionally time individual opens (only when connections are the suspected bottleneck).\n\n3. **`fetch_composer_payload()`** (line 1690) — Time full function (open + query + JSON parse).\n\n4. **`transcript_data_from_composer_payload()`** (line 1722) — Time full function, count bubbles processed, log per-conversation summary (not per-bubble to avoid 21K log lines).\n\n5. **`fetch_bubble_content_from_db()`** (line 1840) — No individual logging (too noisy). Covered by the aggregate timing in `transcript_data_from_composer_payload`.\n\n6. **`get_last_bubble_timestamp()`** (line 1899) — Time full function.\n\n### B. `src/authorship/post_commit.rs`\n\n7. **`collect_context_conversations()`** (line 794) — Wrap each major stage:\n   - `list_all_cursor_conversation_ids` — time + count\n   - `build_workspace_composer_map` — time + workspace count  \n   - Per-conversation loop — accumulate aggregate times for `get_last_bubble_timestamp`, workspace lookup, `fetch_cursor_conversation_from_db`\n   - Total summary line at end:\n     ```\n     [BENCHMARK] collect_context_conversations: total=12.3s, list_ids=0.1s (541 ids), \n     ws_map=0.5s (23 ws), timestamps=8.2s, ws_lookup=1.5s, fetch=2.0s, \n     sqlite_opens=23804, results=12\n     ```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n1. Add connection counter + per-function timing in `agent_presets.rs`\n2. Add aggregate timing in `post_commit.rs:collect_context_conversations()`\n3. Create `cursor_perf.rs` test + register in `main.rs`\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Run the reproduction test against the real 1.6 GB database and confirm it produces timing output\n2. Read `/tmp/git-ai-benchmark.log` and verify per-stage breakdowns appear\n3. Confirm `cargo test` (without `--ignored`) is unaffected — the perf test should be skipped\n4. Confirm `GIT_AI_DEBUG` is off by default — no overhead in normal usage\n",
