            "content": "# Cursor Conversation Storage System\n\nHow Cursor IDE stores conversation data in SQLite databases. Documented 2026-04-15 from empirical analysis of Cursor's `state.vscdb` files and decompiled source (`workbench.desktop.main.js`).\n\n## Database Locations (macOS)\n\n| Database | Path | SQLite Tables |\n|----------|------|---------------|\n| **Global DB** | `~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/globalStorage/state.vscdb` | `cursorDiskKV`, `ItemTable` |\n| **Workspace DBs** | `~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/workspaceStorage/<hash>/state.vscdb` | `cursorDiskKV`, `ItemTable` |\n\nEach workspace directory also has a `workspace.json` with `{\"folder\": \"file:///path/to/project\"}`.\n\nPlatform paths:\n- **Windows**: `%APPDATA%/Cursor/User/...`\n- **Linux**: `~/.config/Cursor/User/...`\n\n## Global DB: `cursorDiskKV` Table\n\nThis is the main conversation content store. All conversations from ALL workspaces are stored here. Schema: `key TEXT UNIQUE, value TEXT`.\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Key Pattern | Content | Count (example) |\n|-------------|---------|-----------------|\n| `composerData:<uuid>` | Full conversation metadata JSON | 364 |\n| `bubbleId:<composer_id>:<bubble_id>` | Individual message content JSON | 18,266 |\n| `messageRequestContext:<composer_id>:<bubble_id>` | Workspace context for a message | 736 |\n\n### `composerData:<uuid>` Structure\n\nLarge JSON blob (can be several KB). Key fields:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"_v\": 14,                          // Schema version (10, 11, 14 observed)\n  \"composerId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"fullConversationHeadersOnly\": [    // Array of bubble headers (current format since April 2025)\n    {\"bubbleId\": \"uuid\", \"type\": 1}   // type 1 = user, type 2 = assistant\n  ],\n  \"isAgentic\": true,\n  \"unifiedMode\": \"agent\",             // \"agent\", \"chat\", \"plan\"\n  \"agentBackend\": \"cursor-agent\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"subagentComposerIds\": [\"uuid\"],    // Child subagent conversation IDs\n  \"subComposerIds\": [],\n  \"workspaceIdentifier\": {            // NEW FIELD - only on conversations created/loaded after ~April 2025 Cursor update\n    \"id\": \"workspace-hash\",\n    \"uri\": {\"$mid\": 1, \"fsPath\": \"/path/to/project\", ...}\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Important**: `workspaceIdentifier` in composerData is NOT reliable for workspace scoping. Only 16/368 conversations had it as of April 15, 2026. This field is only written when a conversation is created on the newest Cursor version. Older conversations never get backfilled.\n\n### `bubbleId:<composer_id>:<bubble_id>` Structure\n\n```json\n{\n  \"text\": \"message content...\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-15T23:24:56.789Z\",   // RFC 3339 timestamp\n  \"modelInfo\": {\"modelName\": \"claude-3.5-sonnet\"},\n  \"toolFormerData\": {                          // Present for tool-use bubbles\n    \"name\": \"edit_file\",\n    \"rawArgs\": \"{\\\"target_file\\\": \\\"...\\\"}\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### `messageRequestContext:<composer_id>:<bubble_id>` \n\nContains workspace context including `projectLayouts[0]` with `listDirV2Result.directoryTreeRoot.absPath`. **Coverage is poor**: only exists for ~30% of conversations, and 0% of conversations not already covered by other methods. Not recommended as a primary workspace lookup method.\n\n## Global DB: `ItemTable`\n\nStores application-level and workspace-level structured data. Schema: `key TEXT UNIQUE, value TEXT`.\n\n### `composer.composerHeaders` (KEY - Best source for workspace mapping)\n\n**Location**: Global DB `ItemTable`, scope -1 (application-level).\n\nContains an object with `allComposers` array. **Every entry has `workspaceIdentifier`** with the full `fsPath`.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"allComposers\": [\n    {\n      \"composerId\": \"uuid\",\n      \"workspaceIdentifier\": {\n        \"id\": \"workspace-hash\",\n        \"uri\": {\"$mid\": 1, \"fsPath\": \"/Users/.../project\"}\n      },\n      \"type\": \"head\",\n      \"unifiedMode\": \"agent\",\n      \"createdAt\": 1713200000000,\n      \"lastUpdatedAt\": 1713205000000,\n      \"totalLinesAdded\": 42,\n      \"totalLinesRemoved\": 5,\n      \"isArchived\": false,\n      \"isBestOfNSubcomposer\": false,\n      \"isDraft\": false,\n      \"name\": \"conversation title\",\n      \"subtitle\": \"...\",\n      \"branches\": [...],\n      ...\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Coverage**: Contains all conversations that have been loaded by Cursor since the feature was added. As of April 15, 2026: 139/368 conversations covered, including ALL conversations active in the last ~5 days. Subagents ARE included and DO have `workspaceIdentifier`.\n\n**How Cursor populates this**: On every save, Cursor calls `vQy()` which stamps `workspaceIdentifier` on every header entry. In non-glass mode: `n.map(i => ({...i, workspaceIdentifier: e}))` where `e` is the current workspace. This means every conversation gets the workspace of whatever window loaded it.\n\n**Filtering**: Cursor's own code uses `P3a()`: `n.filter(t => t.workspaceIdentifier?.id === e.id)` to filter by workspace.\n\n## Workspace DBs: `ItemTable`\n\nEach workspace directory has its own `state.vscdb`. These store per-workspace conversation metadata.\n\n### `composer.composerData` (per-workspace)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"allComposers\": [                          // Older Cursor: populated. Newer Cursor: EMPTY []\n    {\"composerId\": \"uuid\", \"type\": \"head\", \"createdAt\": 1713200000000, ...}\n  ],\n  \"selectedComposerIds\": [\"uuid\", ...],      // Currently open tabs (~5 IDs)\n  \"lastFocusedComposerIds\": [\"uuid\", ...\"],  // Recently focused tabs (~5 IDs)\n  \"hasMigratedComposerData\": true,\n  \"hasMigratedMultipleComposers\": true\n}\n```\n\n**Critical behavior change**: Newer Cursor versions stopped populating `allComposers` in per-workspace DBs. The 3 most recently active workspaces (as of April 2026) all had `allComposers: []`. Older workspaces still have populated arrays. This means the old `allCo