a_from_composer_payload` / `fetch_bubble_content_from_db` — same N+1 bubble fetching (optimizing this is a separate task)\n- `update_prompts_to_latest` — untouched\n- The profiling instrumentation added earlier — keep it\n\n## What to deprecate (leave in place but unused)\n\n- `list_all_cursor_conversation_ids` — no longer called from `collect_context_conversations`\n- `build_workspace_composer_map` / `build_workspace_composer_map_from` — no longer called\n- `get_conversation_workspace_root` — no longer called\n- `get_last_bubble_timestamp` — no longer called from `collect_context_conversations`\n\nThese are still used by tests and the perf test. Don't delete them — they serve as reference and the old tests validate the old behavior.\n\n## Critical Files\n\n- `src/commands/checkpoint_agent/agent_presets.rs` — add new function (~40 lines)\n- `src/authorship/post_commit.rs` — rewrite `collect_context_conversations` body\n- `tests/integration/cursor_perf.rs` — update perf test\n- `tests/integration/cursor.rs` — add test for new function\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `cargo check` passes\n2. `cargo test --test integration cursor` — existing cursor tests still pass\n3. Run `cursor_perf` test with real DB — new function should be significantly faster than old approach\n4. Make a commit in a Cursor workspace with `GIT_AI_DEBUG=1` — verify `[BENCHMARK] collect_context_conversations` shows reduced time\n",
