            "new_string": "## 10. Cursor DB Performance: Profiling + Workspace Scoping Rewrite\n\n### Problem\n\n`collect_context_conversations()` was extremely slow on large Cursor databases. A coworker's 1.6 GB `state.vscdb` with 541 conversations caused `cargo test` to not finish in 2 hours. Profiling on a 482 MB DB (364 conversations) showed:\n- ~3,500 SQLite connection opens per commit (each function opened a new connection)\n- 1.46s wasted on `get_conversation_workspace_root` LIKE queries that found nothing\n- 398ms on `get_last_bubble_timestamp` for all 364 conversations (most irrelevant)\n- Total: ~2.75s for the context conversation collection alone\n\n### Root cause investigation\n\nEmpirical analysis of Cursor's SQLite storage revealed that the old approach (scanning `composerData:*` keys, then workspace-scoping via per-workspace DBs and `messageRequestContext` LIKE queries) was fundamentally inefficient. A new data source was discovered: `composer.composerHeaders` in the global `ItemTable`, which contains all recent conversations with their workspace path (`workspaceIdentifier.uri.fsPath`) already attached. See `documentation/cursor_conversation_db_system.md` for full details.\n\n### Profiling instrumentation added\n\n**File:** `src/authorship/post_commit.rs`\n- Total timer around `post_commit_with_final_state()` \n- Per-stage timing in `collect_context_conversations()` with aggregate counters\n- Per-cursor-agent timing in `update_prompts_to_latest()`\n- All gated behind `GIT_AI_DEBUG=1` using `[BENCHMARK]` prefix → `/tmp/git-ai-benchmark.log`\n\n**File:** `src/commands/checkpoint_agent/agent_presets.rs`\n- Global `AtomicU64` SQLite connection counter (`reset_sqlite_open_count` / `sqlite_open_count`)\n- Per-function timing in `transcript_data_from_composer_payload()` and `get_last_bubble_timestamp()`\n\n**File:** `tests/integration/cursor_perf.rs` (new)\n- `#[ignore]` test that profiles the cursor DB hot path against a real database\n- Auto-detects default macOS Cursor DB path\n\n### Workspace scoping rewrite\n\n**File:** `src/commands/checkpoint_agent/agent_presets.rs`\n\nNew method `list_workspace_conversation_ids(global_db_path, workspace_path)`:\n- Single query: `SELECT value FROM ItemTable WHERE key = 'composer.composerHeaders'`\n- Parses `allComposers` array, filters by `workspaceIdentifier.uri.fsPath` matching the repo path\n- Returns `Vec<(String, u64)>` — composer IDs with `lastUpdatedAt` timestamps (epoch seconds)\n- Covers all recent conversations including subagents (Cursor stamps `workspaceIdentifier` on every header when a workspace is opened)\n\n**Removed methods** (no longer needed):\n- `list_all_cursor_conversation_ids` — replaced by workspace-filtered query\n- `build_workspace_composer_map` / `build_workspace_composer_map_from` — per-workspace DB scanning eliminated\n- `get_conversation_workspace_root` — the expensive LIKE query fallback (was the biggest bottleneck)\n- `get_last_bubble_timestamp` — replaced by `lastUpdatedAt` from headers (no per-conversation DB queries)\n- `cursor_workspace_storage_path` — no longer needed\n\n**File:** `src/authorship/post_commit.rs`\n\n`collect_context_conversations()` rewritten:\n1. Call `list_workspace_conversation_ids(&db_path, &repo_workdir)` — single query\n2. Filter out already-tracked IDs and conversations older than parent commit (using in-memory timestamps)\n3. Fetch transcripts only for remaining conversations\n\n### Performance impact\n\nOld flow: `list_all_ids (1 conn) → workspace_map (21 conns) → for each of 364 ids: timestamp (2 conns) + workspace_lookup (1 conn LIKE query) + fetch (N conns)` = ~3,500 connection opens\n\nNew flow: `list_workspace_ids (1 conn, 1 query) → filter in memory → for matching ids: fetch (N conns)` = ~1 connection for setup + only connections for conversations that actually match\n\n### Tests\n\n- 4 old `build_workspace_composer_map*` tests removed\n- 4 new `list_workspace_conversation_ids*` tests added (filters by workspace, returns timestamps in seconds, no matching workspace, missing headers key)\n- All existing cursor e2e tests pass unchanged\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Logical Implications",
